\begin_layout Standard
From the previous classes was possible to develop the data model in format
 of web semantic ontologies OWL, the classes were related through Object
 Properties and Data properties that allow to link syntactically the associated
 classes in the evaluation of sustainability.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Data and Object properties must have set the rdfs:range to accomplish the
 validation of related classes and some are functional to ensure a relation
 one-to-one.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
DSS Ontology
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Decision support system ontology contains the elements that were abstracted
 from the analysis of DSS systems used by Embrapa Environment in their assessmen
t processes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The assessment software systems which were analysed are: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
SustenAgro system: assessment of agricultural sustainability in sugarcane.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Innova-Tec system: assessment of technological innovation impact.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Nano-Tec system: assessment of nanotechnological impact.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From these systems were identified common elements, which were abstracted
 in the SAD ontology with the purpose to generalize the classes of sustenagro
 ontology, to provide the generation of graphical interfaces.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The identified and modeled classes are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Evaluation Object: class that represents the objects that will be analyzed
 in each assessment process, which will be as individuals this class or
 some subclass of it, in the case of SustenAgro system the Production Unit
 class is subclass of Evaluation Object
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Feature: class that represents the features of an Evaluation Object which
 will be quantified, analyzed and used in the generation of results of the
 assessment process, generally the Features have a numeric property that
 quantify it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Analysis: class that links the assessment result, the name and date of assessmen
t, as well as the Evaluation Object, to represent an assessment 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Value: class that represents the values that are assigned to each instance
 of Feature 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
User: class that represents the system users.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Role: class that represents the user types of the system, relating the permissio
ns of each type, by default has are instantiated the User and Admin roles.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the figure 5 is presents the basic structure of a DSS, with classes that
 were derived from the abstraction of Sustenagro ontology.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
