\begin_layout Standard
The Value class represents the values that are related to each feature of
 Production Unit, which is divided into Categorical and Real classes, in
 the SustenAgro case represents the possibles values that an Indicator or
 Variable may have, the discrete and defined elements as the categorical
 are modeled as class individuals, thereby enabling, restrict the options
 to choose from.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Figure 6 presents the Value class and subclasses modeled, so much Categorical
 for finite set of values and Real for numeric values, as an example is
 Yes/no Class that represents the yes and no values, which are modeled as
 individuals of said class.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each individual of the Value class has the as number property that relates
 a numeric value for define a comparison criteria and provide a format for
 such data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
