\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These classes are complemented with properties as rdfs:range or patterns
 of data that relate the most appropriate widgets in the representation
 of information, and thus provide the generation of graphical user interfaces.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
SustenAgro Ontology was implemented through semantic web technologies that
 enable information retrieval systems in linken open data format, through
 Blazegraph triplestore that supports the SPARQL 1.1 query language.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Domain Specific Language
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sustenagro system define its functionalities through of a Domain Specific
 Language based on ontologies, which is focused on the language of sustainabilit
y experts to be created and edited directly by them, achieves the administration
 of ontologies and the visual representation of the modeled knowledge, through
 the following features to flexibly the generation of graphical user interfaces.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The sustainable concepts formulated by the experts are joining with the
 knowledge of ontology to define an interface of communication between stakehold
ers and computer systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Features supported by DSL are: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Definition of Evaluation Object.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The evaluationObject command defines the structure of evaluation object
 and binds the corresponding visual controls, the command requires an URI
 of the class of elements that will be assessed and each one of related
 properties.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In code 1 presents a part of the DSL which defines the evaluation object
 class Production Unit and the properties through the instance and type
 commands.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float algorithm
placement H
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
evaluationObject ":ProductionUnit", { 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
	instance "ui:hasName', label: ["en": "Name", "pt": "Nome"] 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
	instance ":hasAgriculturalProductionSystem" 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
	type label: ["en": "Type", "pt": "Tipo"] 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
}
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Definition of Evaluation Object 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The instance command links a property through its URI and can be complemented
 by parameters that customise the visual representation of property.
 The type command links the subclasses of main class, to be assigned in
 the evaluation object instances, in the SustenAgro system case, said command
 identifies that the Production Unit instances can also be a Provider or
 a Plant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The parameters that can complement the previous command are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Label: defines an associate text.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Placeholder: defines an help text.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Required: defines a mandatory property.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Widget: defines a user graphical control.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Definition of Feature 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Feature command define the features which will be presented during the
 evaluation to be instantiated as part of Analysis, it has a argument an
 URI that allows to link subclasses of the referenced class, the instances
 of the classes will be quantified by the assessment process, in which it
 is carried out the property has value that links each Feature through URIs
 of classes: EnvironmentalIndicator, EconomicIndicator, SocialIndicator,
 ProductionEfficiencyFeature and TechnologicalEfficiencyFeature.
 Furthermore is possible to add inlcusion of new features in the user graphical
 interface through extraFeatures parameter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float algorithm
placement H
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
feature ':EnvironmentalIndicator', 'extraFeatures': true
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
