\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Definition of assessment logic
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This DSL functionality define the process to assessment the data and generate
 relevant information which be presented as the system output, and can be
 integrated into views and widgets.
 The assessment logic is supported by the logical and mathematical features
 of Java and Groovy languages.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The report command defines the quantitative treatment that will be made
 to the Features, with the purpose to obtain general values or standards
 as result of assessment process, to be presented directly or through widgets
 to facilitate the representation and understanding of assessment system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The following code shows the implementation of the SustenAgro system formula,
 creating variables result of arithmetic operations to generate general
 results, in the case of SustenAgro the code generates the sustainability
 variable that represents the sustainability index.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float algorithm
placement H
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
report {
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
	environment = weightedSum(data.':EnvironmentalIndicator') 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
	economic = weightedSum(data.':EconomicIndicator') 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
	social = weightedSum(data.':SocialIndicator') 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
	sustainability = (environment + social + economic)/3 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
} 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Definition of assessment logic
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Definition of the GUI of the report
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The report command also defines the widgets that make up the visual part
 of the report, which may use the result variables of assessment logic as
 the widgets input, to improve the representation and facilitate the understandi
ng of results.
 In the following code presents an example of use this feature in SustenAgro
 System, in which commands are set to generate the graphical user interfaces,
 as sustainabilityMatrix that uses variables as arguments.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float algorithm
placement H
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
report { 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
	evaluationObjectInfo() 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
	sustainabilityMatrix x: sustainability, y: efficiency text 'en': 'Microregion
 map', 'pt': 'Mapa da microregião' 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
	map data.'Microregion'
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
}
\end_layout

