\begin_layout Section
Architecture
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The use of semantic web ontologies was necessary to represent and organize
 the knowledge and so provides a well-defined structure adaptable to changes,
 however the ontologies lack flexibility to define specific procedures and
 settings.
 Whereby the alternative found to meet this gap is the use of a Domain Specific
 Language based on ontologies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The developed architecture has two ontologies base:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
SustenAgro ontology has the knowledge representation of production units,
 sustainability indicators, sustainability variables, sustainability index,
 analyzes and geographical information.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
DSS ontology contains the main concepts for support the assessment process
 and provides datatypes mapping and support graphical user interfaces.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ontologies are instantiated in a triplestore that supports the storage and
 retrieval of information for the entire system.
 The expert user has access to system configuration through DSLs in which
 are presented according to terminology setup instructions used by the expert
 domain, allowing you to configure system features such as the data that
 make up an object of evaluation, the formulas of sustainability and graphic
 interfaces to present the results.
 Thus, the ‘manager-domain expert’ is able to make changes at any time the
 system is running.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Figure 7 represents the architecture of SustenAgro System, which is based
 on the ontologies and configured by expert users through of the DSL, to
 configure the automatic generating the views for end users.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
placement H
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename images/SustenAgro Arquitecture final.png
	scale 50

\end_inset


\end_layout

