\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
SustenAgro System Architecture.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
SustenAgro system was modularized on elements with defined functionality,
 the main components are the ontologies and DSL defined above, however there
 are other elements which provide features for the system flexibility and
 the graphical user interface generation, these elements are: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ontology Editor: web text editor based on YAML format for provide human-readable
 syntax to define classes, properties and individuals of ontologies, allow
 users to create and edit ontologies in real-time, providing the update
 functionality of critical knowledge which is still in construction such
 as sustainability indicators.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
DSL Editor: web text editor based on expert domain knowledge to define evaluatio
n objects, features, assessment logic and GUIs mapping, allows users to
 create and edit DSL in real-time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Widgets: The system has a collection of generic widgets for support the
 generation of UI views, which can have mandatory inputs to allow its instantiat
ion.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Views: The system has a set of UI views which make use of the widgets for
 define the rendering of each view of the generated web application.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Figure 8 shows the rendering of the view “Production Unit” which is the
 result of the UI generation process presented in the architecture definition,
 this rendering starts with the ontology definitions, then is complemented
 with the DSL specification and is send as input to the view for automatic
 generating of GUI.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This view shows the SustenAgro report and the Sustainability Matrix widget,
 which were generated through the data flow described in the architecture,
 using the ontologies, dsl and views in the generation of report with contains
 the assessment results.
 
\end_layout

